Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.37,0:01:02.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nihon Shogakkan
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.38,0:01:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.93,0:01:15.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toko Credit Cooperative {東光建設信用組合}{horizontal}\NSoka Gakkai Headquarters {創價學會本部}{vertical}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.93,0:01:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finally starting this new business!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The very thought of doing it on my own \Nsends me shuddering! {unsure: 自分にやれるかなと身震いがしてきますよ - probably means "if I had to do it without you, ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, will you really be able to handle this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.12,0:01:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll need you guys \Nto do your best from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.53,0:01:36.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,December 1st:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:40.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda's new financial business,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.52,0:01:44.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toko Credit Cooperative, \Nbegins operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:53.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the executive director of the credit union,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.19,0:01:56.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda was essentially in charge of all aspects of management,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.89,0:02:01.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was burning with a strong determination to get the business back on track
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:04.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and make it a success this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:08.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,March 1950 {1950年(昭和25年)3月—}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.71,0:02:10.08,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,As a sales and negotiations employee at a credit union,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.08,0:02:15.21,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi traveled around town trying to get people to make a deposit at Toko,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.21,0:02:18.69,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,but finance was never really \NShinichi's cup of tea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:22.37,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and it was the one job \Nhe couldn't stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.47,0:02:24.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:28.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,if Toda-sensei thought it necessary and decided to proceed with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.88,0:02:31.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,I also have to do whatever I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.06,0:02:35.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll fight tooth and nail for the rebirth of sensei's business.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.34,0:02:39.35,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Around this time, the effects of the government's enforced
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.34,0:02:39.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,June
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.35,0:02:44.05,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,implementation of the Nine Principles for Economic Stability were evident ubiquitously.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:47.33,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Not only did large companies had to cut back operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:51.85,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,small and medium-sized companies also saw \Na stream of bankruptcies that started last year
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:54.24,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and peaked in the first half of 1950.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:06.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,How inhumane... The full burden of the recession has fallen on small and medium-sized businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.77,0:03:10.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,The companies we've lent to are becoming insolvent in quick succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:16.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,And even those who don't are asking us for a grace period on their repayment more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.73,0:03:19.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,If things continue like this, \Neven if our books are in the black,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:23.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,we may fall short of the critical cash needed for withdrawals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.02,0:03:29.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The world is certainly strapped for money right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.70,0:03:32.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,So much so nobody has any \Nto put into savings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:36.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,But if we can't survive through this, \Nthen we aren't worth our salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.99,0:03:39.09,Top,,0,0,0,,We have some breaking news!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.09,0:03:43.41,Top,,0,0,0,,It appears that fighting has broken out \Nacross the 38th parallel
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:45.72,Top,,0,0,0,,on the Korean Peninsula early this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.72,0:03:46.99,Top,,0,0,0,,Allow me to repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:51.56,Top,,0,0,0,,It appears that fighting broke out early this morning on the Korean Peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:49.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,On June 25, 1950, the Korean War broke out! {1950年(昭和25年)6月25日、朝鮮戦争勃発!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:54.13,Top,,0,0,0,,all across the 38th parallel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.72,0:04:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.74,0:04:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.74,0:04:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's takin' you so long?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.35,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up! \NI was here first!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.44,0:04:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on...? \NNo deposits, all withdrawals!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If this continues, we'll run out of cash!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.34,0:04:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, at this rate, \Na bank run seems more than likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.79,0:04:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the war in Korea broke out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we've had nothing but deposit withdrawals for three days straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:38.88,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The memory of postwar bank deposit freezes \Nwas still fresh in the Japanese minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:38.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,February 1946: The Japanese government promulgates the Financial Emergency Measures Order {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E9%A0%90%E9%87%91%E5%B0%81%E9%8E%96}{昭和21年2月\N日本政府、金融緊急措置令を公布}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.88,0:04:45.26,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,For that reason, out of fear that Japan might be drawn into a war in the neighboring country,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.88,0:04:49.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,"Citizens' deposits are frozen" {probably refers to 1946, so maybe make it "were" to make a clear distinction with 1950}{国民の預金が封鎖される}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.26,0:04:50.35,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the people were dead-set on keeping the money to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the thing, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.16,0:04:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't do something about it, \Nit'll turn real bad real quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.54,0:04:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We are already running low on cash on hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.99,0:05:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.07,0:05:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take immediate action. \NI'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:10.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what can I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:14.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't count on the credit union managers to handle it well. {/are completely unreliable - probably means "they can't stop the bank run" but maybe means "our backers won't support us"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:18.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,Is there any way I can help it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.78,0:05:29.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hold up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.03,0:05:30.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,A merger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.37,0:05:33.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right! That is still an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:38.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,We have no choice but to merge with some union that found itself in a better spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:43.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we manage to do that, even if it means putting myself and the union at a disadvantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:48.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,at the very least, it'll spare our depositors any extra worry. {/we'll be able to proceed without causing ... any trouble}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okumura-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the face of our credit union's current predicament,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:06:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the decision has been made at the board meeting to merge with another union.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.01,0:06:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to proceed in secret.\NI'll manage the merger myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.03,0:06:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Until that is concluded, \NI need you to hold out no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. I'll see what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.93,0:06:33.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,All that work for nothing... \NHow did it come to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:37.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,Things are making a 180 before our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,What to do next?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.16,0:06:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well done. \NHow did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They turned us away everywhere,\Nno matter how many times we asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.48,0:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Nobody wants to bail us out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:06:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also completely helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess... \Nwe'll have to resort to merger, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.54,0:07:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't even listen to me. \NWe're being completely stonewalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:16.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,The company's position might just be \Neven more precarious than it seemed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.25,0:07:21.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've never seen Toda-sensei so distressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.26,0:07:26.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,Les Miserables {レミゼラブル}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:32.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Coming home after midnight again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:37.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Really, I didn't even realize how much it hurt sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:41.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,I feel ashamed that it never even crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:44.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must do whatever I can for sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:46.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must stay strong for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.30,0:07:51.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,When the going gets tough, \Nthe tough get going. {lit: I will face any hardship and any difficulty without hesitation!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:55.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda made every effort \Nto resolve the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.11,0:07:58.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,including asking the Ministry of Finance, \Nthe regulatory agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:08:03.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to mediate their merger with another credit union.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.21,0:08:08.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,August 22nd
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This arrived from \Nthe Ministry of Finance today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A "cease operations" notice. \NEffective tomorrow the 23rd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Signed by the Minister of Finance himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.12,0:08:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.91,0:08:20.86,Overlap,,0,0,0,,What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, starting tomorrow, Toko Credit Cooperative will cease all operations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.20,0:08:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and initiate the bankruptcy proceedings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.37,0:08:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I needed to tell you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, a word from the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As you just heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we have no choice, but to dissolve\Nthe Toko Credit Cooperative tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.56,0:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to apologize to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.51,0:08:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you all worked hard for the union, \Nyet I failed to preserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.14,0:09:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing you could do to stop it.\NBlame all the responsibility on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You all have done so much for me \Nin our turbulent times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to thank you once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.82,0:09:16.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,The next day
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.83,0:09:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.35,0:09:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A reporter from Toto News has come, \Nsaying he wants to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.35,0:09:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him you were away, \Nbut he just won't go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.84,0:09:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. \NLet's meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.84,0:09:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment, Sensei. He came here after hearing about us shutting down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I also overheard that reporter \Ncalling his boss earlier:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've got a hella scoop coming, \Njust you wait!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.62,0:09:45.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,What should I do? \NThe board meeting is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.61,0:09:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei. Allow me to meet him \Non your behalf today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.52,0:09:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sounds good. \NI'm counting on you to handle it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.62,0:09:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, how many \Ndepositors do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I know asking to know the total amount of damages is kinda out of the left field...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But how much in debt are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.39,0:10:09.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,This man is in a hurry to meet the manuscript deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.40,0:10:12.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,I need to buy us some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what'll it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. \NI believe it to be quite a substantial amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.07,0:10:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just yesterday, so only the executive director can tell us the exact details.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's away, isn't he? A rough estimate will suffice. Just to know the general trend, is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But aren't accuracy and precision \Nsupposed to be the essence of journalism?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I guess they are. But you know, time waits for no one. Roughs will do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what'll it be? \NI guarantee you'll like my article. {lit: i won't write badly - maybe "I'll make you look good"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.97,0:10:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my hope. \NI must say you were quite quick to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.85,0:10:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Other newspaper hadn't sent their journalists here as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.98,0:10:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cause I have an excellent intuition. {the wolf knows what the ill beast thinks; it takes one to know one; it takes a thief to catch a thief​}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:56.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi's delaying strategy worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.99,0:11:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, the reporter ran out of time\Nto deliver the scoop he promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was moved to the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.48,0:11:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll just come again tomorrow to ask your executive director for numbers, Yamamoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.25,0:11:12.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Dream}{ignore}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, if you collect all of these unpaid debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be able to cover all your obligations?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. However, we can't do that in a snap of a finger, so we have to bid for time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's what you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in unaware of the true state of things right now, Aoyama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.99,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mean to encroach on your newspaper's right to print anything they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.26,0:11:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.26,0:11:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When word of the cease-and-desist order hit the newspapers, creditors rushed in all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.16,0:11:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, debtors just thought "lucky me, I don't have to pay back my debt anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When this happens, \Nthings tend to truly go out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.53,0:11:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it's the ordinary depositors \Nwho suffer the most from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a regrettable situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.30,0:12:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because we were confident that we would be able to pay our debts off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.52,0:12:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go ahead and submit it now, \NI could end up ruining a lot of people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.77,0:12:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm in a pickle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me put this straight:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you now wield a complete authority over the life or death of our credit union.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:32.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,What strong words, sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.75,0:12:35.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,A single sentence to drive a wedge so deep into one's soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.81,0:12:37.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,What is Aoyama going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, fine, I understand! \NWe'll wait a while before publishing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.84,0:13:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.43,0:13:04.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today we got one journalist \Nto postpone his article...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.85,0:13:07.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,But we're not out of the woods just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.82,0:13:13.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,It is highly likely that another newspaper \Nwill also try to pursue this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:16.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,The crisis is averted for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.67,0:13:21.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what should I do \Nto protect sensei from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.87,0:13:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The sway that newspapers hold over people's minds is amazing nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be a real nuisance if they want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.36,0:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But that also why having even a single newspaper of your own is a very powerful asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.09,0:13:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.35,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep that in mind. {今度のことでよく\N - no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.09,0:13:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We also need to start a newspaper for Soka Gakkai as soon as we have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.29,0:13:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please think it over, Shin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.03,0:13:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:50.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In our days, Seikyo Shimbun \Nrose to the position {meaning in 1995 or whenever this came out}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:53.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of the world's largest religious bulletin. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seikyo_Shimbun}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.12,0:13:54.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The idea for its publication
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.94,0:13:59.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was actually conceived during this turbulent period.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.93,0:14:02.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,Police headquarters {警視庁}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.33,0:14:05.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.95,0:14:07.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,where Makiguchi-sensei and I
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.38,0:14:11.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,were once imprisoned for the crime we didn't commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:18.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Those in power will always \Nabuse it for their own convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.41,0:14:23.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,Underestimating the power this time around \Nwould be a grave mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:29.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,No matter how much flak I personally receive for the collapse of the credit union,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:33.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,no matter how much the authorities \Nor the law are after me, it won't stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.04,0:14:35.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm prepared for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.91,0:14:40.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, I can't put Soka Gakkai in harm's way, \Nwhile they're busy spreading the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:46.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens,\NI must protect the organization at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:48.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,For that purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, faith, practice, and study \Nare our three priorities. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soka_Gakkai#Faith,_practice,_and_study}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.44,0:14:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The combination of practice and study \Nis what constitutes your piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.46,0:15:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, I would like you all to listen carefully to what I have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.06,0:15:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a personal matter that has nothing to do with you directly, but I'd like you to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.09,0:15:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our credit union \Nceased operations yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.07,0:15:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.59,0:15:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.22,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It fell to me to clean up \Nthe mess that remained afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, it has nothing to do with Soka Gakkai,\Nbut it puts me personally into a fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,After a short consideration,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I've arrived at a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.57,0:15:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to resign from my position \Nas the president from today on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.40,0:16:05.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei resigns? But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask Mishima Yoshizo-kun \Nto take over as the board chairman. {effectively it's someone who acts as the head of the organization, but not exactly as present, maybe "acting president"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.43,0:16:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It absolutely doesn't mean \NI've given up on my faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.47,0:16:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My resolve to devote myself to the great cause of the Common Path is still unwavering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, it's this very resolve \Nthat makes me meet those tribulations head-on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:40.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't believe how short-sighted I've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.75,0:16:44.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,I never realized how hard it was for Sensei, \Nwho's struggling with his business...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.21,0:16:50.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,However... \NWhy must he resign as the president?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.63,0:16:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens to me from now on,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.65,0:16:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai must absolutely hold steady \Nand stay true to its journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You must not let the change of leadership \Nupset you in the slightest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.13,0:17:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have also prepared myself fully \Nfor what is to come. {私も自ら 深く心に期するところがあります}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.32,0:17:15.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,"Prepared himself for what's to come?" \NWhat could that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.35,0:17:18.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,Is he going to do something radical?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:22.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's better this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:25.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.41,0:17:30.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the only way to preserve \NSoka Gakkai intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.74,0:17:40.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei is Soka Gakkai itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.39,0:17:45.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Under no circumstances, can I imagine Soka Gakkai without Toda-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.25,0:17:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto here. May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.78,0:17:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:17:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now... What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.90,0:18:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei... If Mishima-san becomes the next president, will that make {\i1}him{\i0} my mentor? {/master/teacher}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.39,0:18:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, by no means!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I may not be the most accommodating mentor, \Nbut I am your mentor. {lit: although I'm a mentor who gives you nothing but trouble/hard work}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:35.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's all I needed to hear...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.32,0:18:40.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Now I don't have to worry about anything else, \Nno matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.24,0:18:46.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Shin is a very noble fellow \Nto care about even such a trifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.28,0:18:53.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,My lifelong mentor is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.71,0:18:55.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.05,0:18:58.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.04,0:19:09.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This day, August 24th, was Yamamoto Shinichi's 3rd anniversary as a member of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:13.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toko Credit Cooperative {東光建設信用組合}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.02,0:19:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.18,0:19:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. See you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.11,0:19:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:15.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.22,0:19:21.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From the next day on, Toda started working on liquidating the credit union.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.20,0:19:24.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At this point, several more employees left the company
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.83,0:19:29.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and Toda had very few personnel remaining in his command.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.89,0:19:37.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's 10 already... I've been to eight houses and only one agreed... {no clue what they agreed for, maybe pay their debt, maybe invest into union}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're up so late, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.02,0:19:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there you are. \NI've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home together. \NIt's late, so you can stay at my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, cider for Yamamoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.19,0:20:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Shin, how about a match of shogi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.65,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so late, what are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. You can go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, bring out the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.71,0:20:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.54,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's play just one for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.52,0:20:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.70,0:20:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! How about this move, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.31,0:20:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks good enough to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:20:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:20:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.74,0:21:05.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,The credit union fell through, and he had to resign as the president of Soka Gakkai...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.12,0:21:08.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yet here he is, completely engrossed by a game of shogi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.04,0:21:15.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,When I see him like this, our every predicament feels like a joke or a distant dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.13,0:21:19.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our current distresses \Nare only temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.15,0:21:22.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,This might just be the Sensei's true form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.80,0:21:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, thinking about unnecessary things doesn't do favors to your concentration!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.16,0:21:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're having fun, enjoy it wholly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.91,0:21:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, when the battle comes, \Nyou'd be well-rested. {unsure what he means by "otherwise you won't be able to fight the big battle", could be "when you're given a time to rest, enjoy it fully, otherwise those unnecessary thoughts will keep haunting you on the battlefield"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Then, how about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.90,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh-ho! This is my answer, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.89,0:21:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.91,0:21:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me my money back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.91,0:21:44.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toko Credit Cooperative {東光建設信用組合}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.34,0:21:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you gonna settle it?! {/what are you going to [about giving me my money]}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When will I receive my deposit already?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.55,0:21:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How long do I have to wait?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.72,0:21:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Uchiyama-kun, please bring the account books to the conference room on the mezzanine floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.27,0:21:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, I owe everyone an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.92,0:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.36,0:22:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.55,0:22:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we manage to collect all these dues from our lenders, we'll be able to repay you all. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.57,0:22:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely ask you to understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.58,0:22:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't want any of that. \NI just need my money, right goddamn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.91,0:22:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just get the money \Nto pay me back in full?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.82,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay us back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.34,0:22:26.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,Kishida Co., Ltd. {岸田商事株式會社}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.83,0:22:33.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda visited Kishida, an old friend, \Nat his company's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.83,0:22:37.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kishida was running \Na wide range of businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.09,0:22:41.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The two were close friends who helped each other on my occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.09,0:22:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I understand. \NYou have my support.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.07,0:22:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like the idea \Nof funding the liquidation,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'd be happy to give you money to start a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.78,0:22:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Kishida-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.87,0:22:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one of the few men I can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.59,0:22:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pay me back \Nwhen you start making profits.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.86,0:23:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a lifesaver for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate it, truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.11,0:23:10.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Wages continued to be delayed, and now even the employees who fought hard so far
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.11,0:23:07.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toko Credit Cooperative {東光建設信用組合}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:10.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Letter of resignation {}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.72,0:23:13.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,were leaving the company one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.71,0:23:18.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,This means our sales department is just Sato-kun and Yamamoto-kun now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.71,0:23:24.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,I don't feel too well,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.51,0:23:27.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,I think I got a fever again. {not from a cold but something that keeps coming back due to his bad lungs}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.56,0:23:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How was your political science exam?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.74,0:23:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, aren't you asking 'cause you wound through it all? {no clue what to make of ヤマばっちり, either it's "perfect score" or "complete guess"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.53,0:23:36.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,I want to study too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.16,0:23:40.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,Once our current troubles are over and things settle down, I'll return to Taisei Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.03,0:23:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.53,0:23:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Five families agreed to make a deposit today. {lit: I got consent from 5 houses}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.72,0:23:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.79,0:24:00.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei looks so tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.04,0:24:05.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda remained composed through all the hardships he endured,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.36,0:24:08.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but his emaciation was now impossible to conceal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.05,0:24:12.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi was also thoroughly exhausted by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.64,0:24:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.16,0:24:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NYou don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.58,0:24:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.78,0:24:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Shin? \NIs your inner strength waning? {actually seimeiryoku is "vitality/life force" but in this context I think he means "one's will to stay strong/determination to be in good health"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.70,0:24:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't win a battle \Nif your inner strength is in decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.96,0:24:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.54,0:24:43.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The emaciated and haggard Master offered an earnest prayer to the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.13,0:24:46.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for the sake of his haggard \Nand beloved disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.80,0:24:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.19,0:24:59.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,Although Sensei is so tired himself, \Nhe is praying for my strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.81,0:25:04.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei... I'm sorry for being such a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.69,0:25:06.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I'm deeply grateful!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.50,0:25:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.08,0:25:21.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Beethoven's Symphony No. 5 in C minor, \N"The Fate Symphony"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.47,0:25:24.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even if it's just me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.22,0:25:30.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will serve and protect Toda-sensei \Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.61,0:25:35.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,That is my mission and fate! {as in symphony name}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.66,0:25:45.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,This should be good enough. \NI'll give it to him tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.13,0:25:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.67,0:25:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good morning. \NShin, did you rest well yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.09,0:25:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't have you lose any more weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.16,0:26:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.26,0:26:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd rather you \Ntake at least a brief break.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.81,0:26:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.80,0:26:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.58,0:26:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei... This is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.99,0:26:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! What do we have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.61,0:26:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Still serving an old and mystic fate, \NThough others change, {actually found this in the English translation of the second volume of human revolution the book, quoting from there}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.73,0:26:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I alter not.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.70,0:26:34.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,Still serving an old and mystic fate,\NThough others change,\NI alter not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.18,0:26:39.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand. \NI really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.55,0:26:44.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Shin!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.25,0:26:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I’ll write a poem too, \Na reply poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.07,0:26:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.01,0:27:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Whenever I stand on fields of war,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.69,0:27:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailing at my side,\NYou are my sword.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.52,0:27:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.16,0:27:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.76,0:27:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.45,0:27:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,one more verse to go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.17,0:27:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"Fading, failing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.66,0:27:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At death, I the king leave to you\NMy crown."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.75,0:27:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There, that should be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.21,0:28:12.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Whenever I stand on fields of war,\NUnfailing at my side,\NYou are my sword. {on the right}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.21,0:28:12.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Fading, failing,\NAt death, I the king leave to you\NMy crown. \N- Josei {left}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:20.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will I really be able to become his sword? \NWill I ever be worthy of Sensei's crown?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.07,0:28:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yes.}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.22,0:28:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.60,0:28:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.75,0:28:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, let's take a short walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.67,0:28:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.25,0:28:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've made a terrible mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.72,0:28:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is happening now is my major punishment from Nichiren Daishonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.83,0:28:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:28:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, never mind that...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.84,0:28:56.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,I am quite certain that I've made some terrible mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.94,0:29:03.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Firstly, while teaching everyone the Lotus Sutra, I mixed in the Tendai interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.95,0:29:07.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,Secondly, the position of Soka Gakkai president
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.20,0:29:12.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,remained formally vacant for five years \Nafter Makiguchi-sensei's death. {hope he means this, not sure: 二つには牧口先生亡き後 5年もの長きにわたって会長を空席のままにしてきたこと}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.87,0:29:18.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,Finally, I was so single-minded
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.63,0:29:23.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,on bolstering our economic strength \Nthat I put the advancement of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.98,0:29:29.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,and the fundamental issue of religious revolution on the back burner.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.43,0:29:37.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,It is only natural that I should reap the wrath of Nichiren Daishonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.29,0:29:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, I made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.15,0:29:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am now going to pray to the Kind Buddha for repentance and atonement of my sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.14,0:29:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What falls on the ground \Ncan only rise up from the ground. {probably his way of saying "when you're at the bottom, the only way is up" }
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.16,0:29:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way to do it is through faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.79,0:30:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, I'll be tutoring you in all of your college studies, starting next Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.75,0:30:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to my house. We must fulfill \Nyour academic aspirations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.47,0:30:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.99,0:30:12.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After this, Toda started his new company \Nand the liquidation work proceeded steadily.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.97,0:30:17.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There was finally an end in sight to the problems that have been plaguing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.10,0:30:20.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the credit union for the past several months.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.01,0:30:29.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was this profound and firm master-disciple bond that Toda Josei and Yamamoto Shinichi
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.05,0:30:34.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,formed through long, arduous, \Nand devoted struggles for their faith, {actually "persevered through single-minded difficult struggle" which is buddhism-specific term for "enduring immeasurable hardships with a single thought of faith - as if condensing the hardships of countless eras into a single moment, so as to cause the wisdom and vitality of the Buddha emerge"; don't think there's english translation or even equivalent for that}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.03,0:30:37.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which became the catalyst for \NSoka Gakkai's rapid growth in our time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.51,0:30:45.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and a source of inspiration for all who work hard for its sake, continuing to live on today.
